text:
(1) Williamsburg Bridge across East River. This view, taken from about A Kent Ave., Brooklyn, shows its construction.

About 1903?.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) A view from the Manhattan side and showing the brick and steel underpinning. The road bed proper is shown projecting eastward to Brooklyn.

March 5, 1937.

Geo. D. Chinn.

(3) The same from an angle.

'Not a dry mount item'

Geo. D. Chinn.

March 5, 1937.

text:
Hewes Street, at the S.E. corner of Kent Ave. The long view of the building is on Hewes Street. In the foreground, is Classon Ave., intersecting with Hewes Street and Kent Ave.

October 1928.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Hewes Street, south side, west from Kent Ave. A view of D. Appleton's old plant. He founded the publishing house bearing his name in 1825.

April 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
